CommitT OS
==========

CommitT is an offline-first, native Android-integrated enforcer built to hard-lock 
digital distractions and drive absolute physical and professional consistency. It 
bypasses standard user-space restrictions to manage native hardware overrides, 
deep OS permissions, and synchronized behavioral accountability.

SECURITY NOTICE: To maintain the integrity of the ecosystem and prevent active 
bypass abuse, the core Kotlin anti-circumvention heuristics and penalty execution 
engines remain closed-source. This repository contains the public-facing architecture, 
native bridges, and synchronization concepts.

Quick Start (Codebase Tour)
---------------------------

* The Core Infrastructure Library: apps/native/lib/
  (Contains the Triple-Write Saga Orchestrator and Offline SQLite Sync Engine)
* The Cloud Backend (Domain-Driven): packages/backend/convex/
  (Houses the Serverless API Edge, Background Schedulers, and DB Schemas)
* The React Native UI / Mobile Client: apps/native/app/
  (Includes the 60fps Heterogeneous FlatList and Tactile Design Systems)
* The Native Android Hardware Bridges: apps/native/modules/
  (JSI bridges to Kotlin Accessibility Services and AlarmManagers)
* The Desktop Dashboard (Tauri/Vite): apps/web/
  (Cross-platform desktop client for managing commitments)
* The Browser Blocker Extension: apps/extension/
  (WXT-based distraction blocker for Chrome/Firefox)

Essential Documentation
-----------------------

All reviewers and engineers should be familiar with:

* Execution Stack: React Native, Expo, Kotlin, SQLite, Convex, Tauri, Vite
* System Philosophy: docs/PHILOSOPHY.md
  (The origin story and the requirement for mathematically unbreakable discipline)
* Security Routing Rules: docs/ARCHITECTURE.md#direct-routing-guide
  (Strict guidelines on dependencies and state mutations)

Documentation can be viewed directly within the docs/ directory.


Who Are You?
============

Find your role below:

* Startup Founder - Evaluating product execution and philosophical drive
* Lead Systems Engineer / CTO - Auditing offline sync, db concurrency, and sagas
* Cloud Backend Architect - Reviewing Domain-Driven Design, Schedulers, and Schemas
* Native Security Expert - Reviewing Android OS-level enforcement and tripwires
* UI/UX Performance Engineer - Investigating tactile interactions and 60fps lists
* Full-Stack Engineer - Reviewing the Web Dashboard and Chrome Extension


For Specific Users
==================

Startup Founder
---------------

Welcome. If you are evaluating this project for high-leverage product execution, 
start your journey here:

* The Origin Story: docs/PHILOSOPHY.md
  (Why most blocker apps fail, and how CommitT enforces a 6:00 AM gym routine)
* The Onboarding Boot Sequence: apps/native/app/index.tsx
  (Cold boot transition handling via Reanimated 3)
* Auth & Session Handling: apps/native/app/(auth)/
  (Secure, offline-capable session management)
* Multi-Step Wizard Flows: apps/native/app/(create-commit)/
  (Complex Zustand state machines governing multi-step commitment creation)

Lead Systems Engineer / CTO
---------------------------

Explore the system's deep internals, bridging protocols, and offline synchronization models:

* Engineering Case Study (The May 8th WAL Collision): apps/BugReport/SyncBug.txt
  (Forensic analysis of SQLite WAL contention between Native and JS threads)
* The Triple-Write Saga Orchestrator: apps/native/lib/triple-write-orchestrator.ts
  (Distributed transaction logic ensuring Cloud ➔ Disk ➔ Hardware consistency)
* Core Local SQLite Engine: apps/native/lib/sync-engine.ts & local-db.ts
  (Atomic "Nuke & Pave" schemas and write-gate queueing)
* Database Mutex Locks: apps/native/lib/sync-lock.ts
  (Preventing cross-thread data races)
* Offline Hydration Lifecycle: apps/native/components/system/HydrationEngine.tsx
  (Restoring global state from disk on boot)
* Connection Watchdog & Resurrection: apps/native/providers/ResurrectionProvider.tsx
  (Self-healing WebSocket and DB handle recovery)
* Expo Native Plugins: apps/native/plugins/withAlarmPermissions/
  (AST manipulation of AndroidManifest.xml during build)

Cloud Backend Architect
-----------------------

Review the Domain-Driven Design (DDD) of the Convex Cloud execution engine:

* The Database Schema (The Steel Vault): packages/backend/convex/db/schema.ts
  (500+ lines of strictly typed schemas, including the immutable Strict Lock Zone)
* Core Domain Logic: packages/backend/convex/core/
  (Separation of concerns across Waivers, Penalties, and Enforcement)
* The Self-Healing Watchdog Engine: packages/backend/convex/execution/watchdog.ts
  (Background cron that identifies and re-syncs orphaned commitments)
* Automated Schedulers (Crons): packages/backend/convex/crons.ts
  (Time-based penalty execution)
* The Public API Edge Handlers: packages/backend/convex/api/
  (Client-facing mutation and query boundaries)

Native Security Expert
----------------------

Security documentation, native tripwires, and hardening guides:

* The Kotlin Enforcer Modules: apps/native/modules/
  (The interface layer connecting JS to native Android APIs)
* Security Shield Overlay & Lockdown: apps/native/components/system/SecurityShield.tsx
  (Mid-render React bounds checking to prevent UI bypasses)
* Native Penalty Triggers: apps/native/app/(penalties)/
  (Email dispatch, Financial penalties, and Embarrassing Photo uploads)
* App Lister Module (Native JSI): apps/native/modules/app-lister-module/
  (High-speed extraction of installed packages and icons via JSI)
* Neutralizing Memory Leaks: docs/ENGINEERING_WINS.md#1-neutralizing-android-native-memory-leaks-oom
  (How an 82% memory reduction was achieved by optimizing SQLite transaction boundaries)

UI/UX Performance Engineer
